   An intestinal operation to lower the cholesterol of heart attack patients reduced their risk for another heart attack or death from heart disease, researchers said today.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The surgery, called a partial ileal bypass, has one significant drawback: It causes chronic diarrhea that persists for years.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   In the operation, doctors change the route of the small intestine so about one-third of it is bypassed.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The $52 million, 17-year study was conducted on people who had already suffered heart attacks.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   The approach lengthened the lives of people who had very mild heart attacks but not those with more severe heart damage.
